<h2><a name="precision" id="precision">precision</a></h2>
<div class="level2">

<p>
Syntax:
</p>
<pre class="c code c++" style="font-family:monospace;">    streamsize ostream<span class="sy0">::</span><span class="me2">precision</span><span class="br0">&#40;</span><span class="br0">&#41;</span>;
    streamsize ostream<span class="sy0">::</span><span class="me2">precision</span><span class="br0">&#40;</span>streamsize p<span class="br0">&#41;</span>;</pre>
<p>

The precision() function either sets or returns the current number of digits that is displayed for floating-point variables.
For example, the following code sets the precision of the cout stream to 5:
</p>
<pre class="c code c++" style="font-family:monospace;">     <span class="kw4">float</span> num <span class="sy0">=</span> <span class="nu16">314.15926535</span>;
     <a href="http://www.opengroup.org/onlinepubs/009695399/functions/cout.html"><span class="kw3">cout</span></a>.<span class="me1">precision</span><span class="br0">&#40;</span> <span class="nu0">5</span> <span class="br0">&#41;</span>;
     <a href="http://www.opengroup.org/onlinepubs/009695399/functions/cout.html"><span class="kw3">cout</span></a> <span class="sy0">&lt;&lt;</span> num;</pre>
<p>

This code displays the following output:
</p>
<pre class="c code c++" style="font-family:monospace;">     <span class="nu16">314.16</span></pre>
<p>
Related Topics: <a href="fill" class="wikilink1" title="io:fill">fill</a>, <a href="width" class="wikilink1" title="io:width">width</a>
</p>

